Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: Studies of inelastic scattering of 185 MeV protons on carbon.

x4freetext: Studies of inelastic scattering of 185 MeV protons
on carbon.
The polyethylene target was used.
Radius of curvature is 94 cm.
.A telescope of three scintillators in
coincidence to detect the particles after magnetic
analyser.
The beam is monitored by a telescope of three
scintillators which counts scattered protons from the
aluminum window at the exit of the proton tube. The
monitor is calibrated with a Faraday Cup.
/by Authors/.The average scattering energy is about 182
MeV. The energies of the plotted spectra are taken in
the center of Mass System. The cross sections and the
angles, however, are plotted in the laboratory system,
as these are the quantities of direct experimental
interest. A plot in the Center of Mass system would not
have been much different.
